{"body": "I still like the `#prepare` method, here is why:\n\n* It uses `#include`, which is a private method.\n* It hides the \"bug\" (unexpected behaviour) in Ruby that `#include` includes modules from right to left. Let's say I call `include BaseHelper, ExtendHelper` I would assume that `ExtendHelper` is included after `BaseHelper`, which is not! `#prepare` would provide that.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/6541557", "created_at": "2012-06-25T07:56:25Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6826#issuecomment-6541557", "updated_at": "2012-06-25T07:57:36Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6826, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/apotonick/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/apotonick/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/apotonick/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/apotonick", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/apotonick/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/apotonick", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/apotonick/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/0fe13386ba69a128e9fadc19ae9d96be?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fda97f65bd113e490a5fab20c4a69f586.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/apotonick/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/apotonick/received_events", "gravatar_id": "0fe13386ba69a128e9fadc19ae9d96be", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/apotonick/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "apotonick", "type": "User", "id": 10406, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/apotonick/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523803c3bd3543c15100c4ae"}, "id": 6541557, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6826"}
